-- Carlyle buys majority stake in Indian publishing services firm
-- By Indulal PM
-- Tue Dec 09, 2014 03:01AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Dec 9 (Reuters) - Private-equity firm Carlyle Group LP <CG.O> said it bought a majority stake in India's Newgen KnowledgeWorks, a provider of publishing and technical services, for $32.8 million.

Carlyle acquired a 54.8 percent stake in the Chennai-based company through First Carlyle Ventures III, an investment fund advised by the Carlyle Group, the U.S. firm said on Tuesday. Carlyle, which manages $203 billion globally, bought shares from Franklin Templeton Private Equity, Aureos South Asia Fund and ePlanet Capital, it said in a statement. Carlyle had earlier invested in Newgen in 2004 and exited in 2011.